---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro'
import BackButton from '../../../components/BackButton.astro'
import DescriptionCard from '../../../components/DescriptionCard.astro'
import CodePreviewCard from '../../../components/CodePreviewCard.astro'
import DescriptionCardHeader from '../../../components/DescriptionCardHeader.astro'
import DescriptionCardText from '../../../components/DescriptionCardText.astro'
import DescriptionCardExampleLink from '../../../components/DescriptionCardExampleLink.astro'
import TopicPageNavbar from '../../../components/TopicPageNavbar.astro'
---

<Layout title="JS Cheat Sheet | Class manipulation">
    <TopicPageNavbar>
        <h1 class="logo">
            <span>JS</span> Cheat Sheet
        </h1>
        <BackButton className="back-button" id="back_button" href="/first_semester/" buttonText="Back to overview"/>
    </TopicPageNavbar>

    <div class="container desc-container">
        <DescriptionCard class="card what-card">
            <div class="card what-card">
                <DescriptionCardHeader class="what-header" headerText="Class manipulation"/>

                <DescriptionCardText>
                    Class manipulation is all about adding or removing <span class="class">classes</span> from an <span class="element">element</span>. Example given, when you open a mobile menu by pressing the three lines, a <span class="class">class</span> is being added that controls the display of the menu. The most important <span class="method">methods</span> for class manipulation are <span class="method">.add<span class="parentheses">()</span></span>, <span class="method">.remove<span class="parentheses">()</span></span>, and <span class="method">.toggle<span class="parentheses">()</span></span>. Examples on these <span class="method">methods</span> can be found <DescriptionCardExampleLink href="https://codepen.io/Schweitz/pen/GRbpZeg" linkText="here." target="_blank"/>
                </DescriptionCardText>
            </div>
        </DescriptionCard>

        <DescriptionCard class="card syntax-card">
            <div class="card syntax-card">
                <DescriptionCardHeader class="syntax-header" headerText="Syntax" />

                <DescriptionCardText>
                    Since these <span class="method">methods</span> are similar to <span class="event-type">eventlisteners</span>, the syntax is the same. First comes the <span class="name">name of the variable</span> followed by <span class="property">.classList</span>. After this comes a period and then the <span class="name">name</span> of the <span class="method">method</span> you wish to use. Inside the <span class="parentheses">parentheses</span> comes a pair of <span class="quote">quotes</span> containing the name of the <span class="class">class</span>, with which you wish to manipulate.
                </DescriptionCardText>
            </div>

            <CodePreviewCard>
                <h3>
                    <pre>

                        <span class="name">variabelNavn</span><span class="method">.metodeNavn
                            <span class="parentheses">(</span><span class="quote">'</span><span class="event-type">klassenavn</span><span class="quote">'</span><span class="parentheses">)</span>
                        </span>
                    </pre>
                </h3>
            </CodePreviewCard>
        </DescriptionCard>
    </div>
</Layout>
